  <original-body>In development mode on each request I18n.reload! is called. If you use a custom backend that e.g. loads all translations from a database this will significantly slow down development.

Attached patches for 2-3-stable and rails 3 add the option config.i18n.reload_on_each_request, which is default set to +false+. In environment/development.rb it is set to +true+ by default.</original-body>
